
Peru and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) signed political and economic agreements
during a visit of the UAE's foreign minister to the South American country on
Monday.

UAE's Foreign Minister Sheikh Abdullah bin Zayed Al Nahyan said his visit to
Peru reflected his country's will to strengthen relations with Peru, especially
economic ones.

Sheikh Abdullah signed an agreement to boost the UAE's investment in Peru.

According to Peru's Foreign Minister Jose Garcia, Peru would host the 3rd Summit
of the Arab-South American Countries in 2011.
